<h1>GRADE POINT AVERAGE (GPA) POLICY:</h1>
<hr>

<!-- <a href="index.html" title="Go Back">Go back</a> -->

<h2>1.	Introduction </h2>
<ul>
<li>
This policy highlights the factors that need to be considered while calculating Semester and Cumulative GPA of students at Habib University.  
</li>
</ul>

<h2>2.	CalculatingSGPA / CGPA </h2>
<ul>
<li>2.1	Grades A+ to F earned in a course shall be counted towards the calculation of SGPA and CGPA.</li>
<li>2.2	Grade F replaced by R or R*, upon repeating a course, shall not be counted towards the calculation of GPA/SGPA.</li>
<li>2.3	In case of Change in Major, all grades, including F, earned in the previous major shall also be counted for the calculation of CGPA.</li>
<li>2.4	Following grades shall not be counted towards the calculation of SGPA or CGPA: Audit (A), Withdraw (W), Incomplete (I), Transfer (T), Suspended (S), Credit (CR), Non-Credit (NCR).</li>
</ul>
